               <floruit notBefore="1400" precision="medium">The Stephanites or <foreign xml:lang="gez">daqiqa  ʾƎsṭifānos</foreign> were a religious movement 
                  within Ethiopian monasticism named after their
                  founder and spiritual leader 
                  <persName ref="PRS3894estifano">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName> ʾƎsṭifānos</persName>. 
                  The movement rose to prominence in the 15th century and continued until the 16th century. 
                  They were persecuted under the order of 
                  
                  <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY"> 
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>. 
                  The Stephanites contributed considerably to the literary production in medieval Ethiopia.
               </floruit>
